      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "OREGON CALDWELL (7) was below best last time but prior to that was narrowly beaten when sixth (17.62) in a Special conditions race at this track. Safe beginner but wide box to overcome and will need some luck. Looks suited here and big improvement expected. WAY COOL (2) was always prominent from this same draw last time and boxed on well to place (22.94) in a Special conditions race over 400m at this track. Good beginner and aided by a handy draw. Harder here but expected to feature again. BLUE MOON MARIE (3) chased the lead early from the inside and boxed on well to finish third, beaten 5.5 lengths (29.91) at this track in a Grade 5 over 512m. Comes through a solid form race last start. Expecting another good run. VOSS ALI (1) was out of the money here last time out but can bounce back.",
